      "content": "While warm compresses and eye drops can provide temporary relief, if you suspect you have conjunctivitis, over-the-counter (OTC) treatments may worsen the condition. Conjunctivitis can be caused by bacteria, viruses, or allergens, and OTC drops may not target the underlying cause. Considering your concerns about cost and time, it's still recommended to consult with an eye care professional to get a proper diagnosis and treatment plan.",
